## Performance Considerations

### Optimization
- Minimize re-renders with useCallback
- Use React.memo for expensive components (if needed)
- Lazy load map tiles
- Debounce search inputs
- Cache computed statistics

### Memory
- Clear unused game data periodically
- Limit trivia history storage
- Compress shared community data
- Monitor LocalStorage size (5MB limit)

## Security Notes

### Safe to Modify
✅ Component logic
✅ Styling and design
✅ Data arrays (teams, venues)
✅ New features
✅ UI improvements

### Be Careful With
⚠️ LocalStorage keys (breaking changes)
⚠️ External CDN URLs (version conflicts)
⚠️ Data schemas (backward compatibility)
⚠️ Critical user data handling

### Never Do
❌ Remove CDN script tags
❌ Break LocalStorage structure
❌ Add tracking/analytics
❌ Transmit user data externally
❌ Remove data validation

## Debugging

### Console Commands
```javascript
// View all games
JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('deepseats-games'))

// View profile
JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('deepseats-profile'))

// Clear all data
localStorage.clear()

// Check React version
console.log(React.version)
```

### Common Errors
- "React is not defined" → CDN didn't load
- "localStorage is not available" → Incognito mode
- "Cannot read property of undefined" → Data migration needed
- Map errors → Internet connection or Leaflet CDN

## Best Practices for Claude Code

1. **Read First**
   - Understand existing code before changing
   - Check component dependencies
   - Review data structures

2. **Incremental Changes**
   - Make small, testable changes
   - Test after each modification
   - Don't refactor everything at once

3. **Preserve Functionality**
   - Maintain existing features
   - Don't break user data
   - Keep UI patterns consistent

4. **Document Changes**
   - Add comments for complex logic
   - Update README if needed
   - Note breaking changes

5. **Test Thoroughly**
   - Run local server
   - Test in multiple browsers
   - Verify data persistence
   - Check responsive design

